  "response": "Here's a brief overview of the muscles in the arm, forearm, wrist, and palm:\n\nArm Muscles:\n1. Biceps brachii - flexes elbow and supinates forearm\n2. Triceps brachii - extends elbow\n3. Brachialis - assists in elbow flexion\n\nForearm Muscles:\nAnterior (Flexor) Compartment:\n1. Flexor carpi radialis\n2. Flexor carpi ulnaris\n3. Palmaris longus\n4. Flexor digitorum superficialis\n5. Flexor digitorum profundus\n\nPosterior (Extensor) Compartment:\n1. Extensor carpi radialis longus\n2. Extensor carpi radialis brevis\n3. Extensor carpi ulnaris\n4. Extensor digitorum\n5. Extensor indicis\n\nWrist Muscles:\n1. Flexor and extensor muscles of the forearm\n2. Radial and ulnar deviation muscles\n\nPalm Muscles:\n1. Thenar muscles (thumb)\n2. Hypothenar muscles (little finger)\n3. Interossei muscles\n4. Lumbrical muscles\n\nThese muscles control movement, flexion, extension, and fine motor skills of the arm, forearm, wrist, and hand.",
